cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks for automated segmentation in cardiac magnetic resonance imaging, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of fully convolutional networks and the development of a new architecture also suggest the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging (cs.MM) and potentially neural engineering (cs.NE) due to its focus on cardiac function.
